- Readyness probe
    - I believe this is a flag

    - continually ping the app in the container before the pod is started up
        - waits until it gets back a 200 from its ping

    - this makes sure the app is ready before it starts sending web traffic


- liveness probe
    - when the liveness fails, the pod is restarted
    - "doesn't try to kill it, just tries to kick it"
    

- kubctl describe
    - used to tell what kubernetes thinks about a particular pod


- K3S: lightweight baremetal kubernetes for local run
